      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Quantum entanglement is a phenomenon where two particles become linked, so the state of one instantly influences the state of the other, regardless of distance. It's not just correlation; it's a deeper connection that defies classical physics. This connection is stronger than any classical correlation, which is why entangled particles can exhibit correlations that cannot be explained by classical theories. It's like two synchronized dancers who move in perfect harmony, even when they're on opposite sides of the world. This mysterious connection is what makes quantum entanglement so intriguing and different from classical correlations. You'll find this concept crucial for understanding the non-locality and the spooky action at a distance that Einstein famously referred to.",
